\begin_layout Proof
GHZ construction (
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\mathcal{H}\right|\ge6$
\end_inset

): Consider three observers with one particle each.
 Each observer can measure two properties, call them X and Y, with outcomes
 
\begin_inset Formula $\pm1$
\end_inset

.
 The associated operators are 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{\sigma}_{x}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{\sigma}_{y}$
\end_inset

.
 The state of the system is 
\begin_inset Formula $\sqrt{2}\left|\chi_{G}\right\rangle =\left|000\right\rangle -\left|111\right\rangle $
\end_inset

 and we also define 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{A}:=\hat{\sigma}_{x}\otimes\hat{\sigma}_{y}\otimes\hat{\sigma}_{y}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{A}\left|\chi_{G}\right\rangle =\left|\chi_{G}\right\rangle $
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{B}:=\hat{\sigma}_{y}\otimes\hat{\sigma}_{x}\otimes\hat{\sigma}_{y}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{C}:=\hat{\sigma}_{y}\otimes\hat{\sigma}_{y}\otimes\hat{\sigma}_{z}$
\end_inset

.
 A measurement of 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{A}$
\end_inset

 would correspond to measurement of property 
\begin_inset Formula $X,\,Y$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

 by the three observers respectively.
 For map 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 consistent with measurement outcomes of QM, we must have 
\begin_inset Formula $m(\hat{A})=m(\hat{B})=m(\hat{C})=+1$
\end_inset

.
 Property (b) of the map 
\begin_inset Formula $\implies1=m(\hat{A}\hat{B}\hat{C})=m(\hat{\sigma}_{x}\otimes\hat{\sigma}_{y}\hat{\sigma}_{x}\hat{\sigma}_{y}\otimes\hat{\sigma}_{x})=m(\hat{\sigma}_{x}^{(1)})m(\hat{\sigma}_{y}^{(2)}\hat{\sigma}_{x}^{(2)}\hat{\sigma}_{y}^{(2)})m(\hat{\sigma}_{x}^{(3)})=m(\hat{\sigma}_{x}^{(1)})m(\hat{\sigma}_{x}^{(2)})m(\hat{\sigma}_{x}^{(3)})=m(\hat{D}\equiv\hat{\sigma}_{x}\otimes\hat{\sigma}_{x}\otimes\hat{\sigma}_{x}),$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{\sigma}_{x}^{(1)}\equiv\hat{\sigma}_{x}\otimes\hat{\mathbb{I}}\otimes\hat{\mathbb{I}}$
\end_inset

 and so on.
 It must be stressed that although 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{A}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{B}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{C}$
\end_inset

 mutually commute, 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{\sigma}_{2}^{(2)},\hat{\sigma}_{y}^{(2)}$
\end_inset

 do not.
 We used property (b) over both these sets of operators in the previous
 step.
 Returning to the argument, note that 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{D}\left|\chi_{G}\right\rangle =-\left|\chi_{G}\right\rangle $
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\implies m(\hat{D})=-1$
\end_inset

 which yields a contradiction.
 We therefore conclude that no 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 with the said properties exists which is consistent with all predictions
 of QM.
\end_layout

