 It follows that 
\begin_inset Formula $\exists$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\mathbf{b}=\left(b_{1}^{(l_{1})},b_{2}^{(l_{2})},\dots b_{n}^{(l_{n})}\right)\right\rangle $
\end_inset

 s.t.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{B}_{i}\left|\mathbf{b}\right\rangle =b_{i}^{(l_{i})}\left|\mathbf{b}\right\rangle $
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $l_{i}$
\end_inset

 indexes the eigenvalues corresponding to 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{B}_{i}$
\end_inset

 and that 
\begin_inset Formula $\sum_{\mathbf{b}}\left|\mathbf{b}\right\rangle \left\langle \mathbf{b}\right|=\hat{\mathbb{I}}$
\end_inset

.
