\begin_inset Formula $\hat{C}\left|\psi\right\rangle =c\left|\psi\right\rangle $
\end_inset

, by assumption.
 For the statement to follow, one need only show that 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\psi\right\rangle $
\end_inset

 must be made of only those 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\mathbf{b}\right\rangle $
\end_inset

s, which satisfy 
\begin_inset Formula $c=f(b_{1}^{(l_{1})},b_{2}^{(l_{2})},\dots b_{n}^{(l_{n})})$
\end_inset

.
 This is the crucial step.
 Proving this is so is trivial.
 We start with 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{C}\left|\psi\right\rangle =c\left|\psi\right\rangle $
\end_inset

 and take its inner product with 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\langle \mathbf{b}\right|$
\end_inset

